Headline: Machine Learning Engineer at Meta
About:
During my graduate research in astrophysics I uncovered the first evidence of a free-floating planet while mining a dataset of gravitational microlensing events. Later, I became fascinated with a formidable modeling problem needed to better understand blackhole accretion disks. This required building and efficiently scaling a distributed simulation that performs random lookups spanning a large supercomputer cluster. My Ph.D. advisor discouraged me from working on it fearing that it was too difficult. Despite the challenges and his doubts, I persisted and solved it. This experience taught me that the computer science and data science aspects of my research were more interesting to me than science of astrophysics.

Next, I re-entered the tech industry with a mixture of consulting for clients, leading an applied research team, and exploring a variety of side projects while at Gravity Jack. Machine learning became my focus. This included organizing a meet up to help inspire and educate others in ML and deep learning. Also, I built a deep learning regression model to estimate the pose of objects seen from a monocular camera which included the development of a variety of novel data collection and data generation techniques.

Now at Meta, I've worked in retrieval and ranking and now on modeled reporting.

Headline: Make data useful
About:
Data science is a unique blend of science and craftsmanship.

At its core, the scientific aspect follows a methodical learning process. It involves constructing a growing body of knowledge based on hypotheses that can be proven false.

On the other hand, the craft aspect embodies our collective intuition, honed through daily problem-solving and validating our hypotheses against real-world outcomes.

Through this process, we develop a comprehensive understanding of what needs to be done, what works effectively, and how to tackle larger challenges.

A good data scientist possesses a good world model.

Having arrived in the United States at the age of 14, I have been greatly influenced by both Eastern and Western cultures. I spent two years in Kansas for high school and two years in the Bay Area for community college, where I was elected as the youngest and first Chinese student body president in college history at age 17.

After completing my undergraduate studies in Economics and working for a year, I decided to return to school and enhance my technical background. My post-graduation aspirations involve pursuing roles in Data science and Product Management.

Prior to UCLA, I served as the President of Ca√±ada College, representing over 6,500 students. While maintaining a high standard of academic excellence, I managed a diverse team comprising 40% of international students and 60% of historically underrepresented students. Together, we organized more than 20 campus-wide events. I led my team in drafting the college's first-ever housing resolution to provide university housing for low-income students. This resolution is currently under review by the College Presidents and District Board of Trustees and, upon approval, will be passed on to the Redwood City Council.

At UCLA, I continued my commitment to student advocacy after being selected by the President to serve as his Chief of Staff. I successfully managed three impactful platforms, including a strategic partnership with residential leads to reduce laundry costs from $2.75 to $1.50 for the next 20 years, resulting in over $500,000 in annual savings for on-campus residents. I was also chosen as the only representative from China to be an inaugural member of the UCLA Chancellor's Leadership, Innovation, Networking, and Knowledge (LINK) program, which provided me with an opportunity to network with industry-leading professionals and social movement leaders from around the world, including billionaire philanthropist Meyers Luskin.

In my free time, I enjoy cooking (you can find me on Instagram @Luka_sauce), competing in E-sports (Top 0.5% in Global NBA2k Gaming), practicing traditional Chinese tea art, playing basketball, singing, and modeling.

I would love to connect with you! Please feel free to reach out to me at juyiyang30@gmail.edu.
